# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# AXILER — Figma-to-Code Rules (Next.js 16 · Tailwind CSS v4 · React 19)
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#
# PURPOSE: Enforce a 100% pixel-perfect Figma replication workflow.
# Every section you build MUST match the Figma frame exactly — spacing,
# typography, colors, breakpoints, and interactions.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## 0 · GOLDEN RULES (read first, always)

1. **NEVER use raw / arbitrary values** (e.g. `w-[347px]`, `text-[#3a86ff]`, `mt-[22px]`).
   Every value MUST come from the Tailwind design-token system defined in
   `globals.css` via `@theme inline { }`. If a Figma value doesn't map to an
   existing token, **add a new token first**, then reference it.
2. **Mobile-first, always.** Default styles target the smallest viewport.
   Layer up with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, and `2xl:` prefixes.
3. **Section-by-section.** Each Figma frame/section becomes its own component.
   Never build the entire page in one file.
4. **Pixel-perfect fidelity.** Match fonts, sizes, weights, line-heights, letter
   spacing, colors, border-radii, shadows, and spacing 1:1 with Figma.
5. **Zero layout shift.** Every image/media must have explicit `width` and
   `height` or use `aspect-ratio` tokens to prevent CLS.


## 1 · TECH STACK & VERSIONS

| Layer       | Tech                   | Version    |
|-------------|------------------------|------------|
| Framework   | Next.js (App Router)   | 16.x       |
| UI Library  | React                  | 19.x       |
| Language    | TypeScript             | 5.x        |
| Styling     | Tailwind CSS           | 4.x        |
| PostCSS     | @tailwindcss/postcss   | 4.x        |
| Icons       | react-icons            | latest     |
| Fonts       | next/font/google       | built-in   |

- Tailwind v4 uses the **CSS-first** configuration model. There is **NO
  `tailwind.config.ts`**. All customisation lives inside `globals.css` under
  `@theme inline { }`.


## 2 · PROJECT STRUCTURE

```
axiler/
├── app/
│   ├── globals.css          ← design tokens + base styles
│   ├── layout.tsx           ← root layout (fonts, metadata, providers)
│   ├── page.tsx             ← home page (assembles sections)
│   └── (routes)/            ← additional pages via route groups
├── components/
│   ├── sections/            ← Figma section components
│   │   ├── shared/          ← sections used across multiple pages
│   │   │   ├── CTA.tsx
│   │   │   └── Footer.tsx
│   │   ├── home/            ← sections specific to the home page
│   │   │   ├── Hero.tsx
│   │   │   ├── Features.tsx
│   │   │   ├── Pricing.tsx
│   │   │   └── Testimonials.tsx
│   │   └── (other-pages)/   ← sections for other pages
│   ├── ui/                  ← atomic UI primitives
│   │   ├── Button.tsx
│   │   ├── Badge.tsx
│   │   ├── Card.tsx
│   │   ├── Input.tsx
│   │   ├── SectionWrapper.tsx
│   │   └── …
│   ├── layout/              ← structural layout components
│   │   ├── Navbar.tsx
│   │   ├── Container.tsx
│   │   └── …
│   └── shared/              ← reusable composed components
│       ├── LogoCloud.tsx
│       ├── SocialLinks.tsx
│       └── …
├── lib/
│   ├── constants.ts         ← site-wide constants (nav links, etc.)
│   ├── types.ts             ← shared TypeScript types/interfaces
│   └── utils.ts             ← helper functions (cn(), formatters, etc.)
├── public/
│   ├── images/              ← optimised static images
│   └── icons/               ← custom SVG icons (not in react-icons)
├── hooks/                   ← custom React hooks
│   ├── useMediaQuery.ts
│   ├── useIntersectionObserver.ts
│   └── …
└── ...config files
```

### File naming rules
- **Sections** → `PascalCase.tsx` inside `components/sections/{page or shared}/`
- **Components** → `PascalCase.tsx` inside `components/{ui,layout,shared}/`
- **Utilities / hooks** → `camelCase.ts`
- **One component per file.** Co-locate types, sub-components and local helpers
  only when they are exclusively used by that component.


## 3 · DESIGN TOKENS (globals.css)

All Figma design values are encoded as Tailwind v4 theme tokens inside
`globals.css`. This is the **single source of truth** for the design system.

```css
@import "tailwindcss";

/* ── CSS Variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
:root {
  /* Backgrounds */
  --background: #ffffff;
  --foreground: #171717;

  /* Brand Palette — extract exact hex values from Figma */
  --brand-primary: #TO_BE_SET;
  --brand-primary-light: #TO_BE_SET;
  --brand-primary-dark: #TO_BE_SET;
  --brand-secondary: #TO_BE_SET;
  --brand-accent: #TO_BE_SET;

  /* Neutrals */
  --neutral-50: #fafafa;
  --neutral-100: #f5f5f5;
  --neutral-200: #e5e5e5;
  --neutral-300: #d4d4d4;
  --neutral-400: #a3a3a3;
  --neutral-500: #737373;
  --neutral-600: #525252;
  --neutral-700: #404040;
  --neutral-800: #262626;
  --neutral-900: #171717;
  --neutral-950: #0a0a0a;

  /* Semantic */
  --success: #22c55e;
  --warning: #f59e0b;
  --error: #ef4444;
  --info: #3b82f6;

  /* Shadows — match Figma shadow tokens */
  --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.05);
  --shadow-md: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1), 0 2px 4px -2px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
  --shadow-lg: 0 10px 15px -3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1), 0 4px 6px -4px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
  --shadow-xl: 0 20px 25px -5px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1), 0 8px 10px -6px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);

  /* Border radii */
  --radius-sm: 0.25rem;
  --radius-md: 0.5rem;
  --radius-lg: 0.75rem;
  --radius-xl: 1rem;
  --radius-2xl: 1.5rem;
  --radius-full: 9999px;
}

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --background: #0a0a0a;
    --foreground: #ededed;
    /* Override any other light-specific tokens here */
  }
}

/* ── Tailwind v4 Theme Tokens ──────────────────────────────────── */
@theme inline {
  /* Colors */
  --color-background: var(--background);
  --color-foreground: var(--foreground);
  --color-brand-primary: var(--brand-primary);
  --color-brand-primary-light: var(--brand-primary-light);
  --color-brand-primary-dark: var(--brand-primary-dark);
  --color-brand-secondary: var(--brand-secondary);
  --color-brand-accent: var(--brand-accent);
  --color-neutral-50: var(--neutral-50);
  --color-neutral-100: var(--neutral-100);
  --color-neutral-200: var(--neutral-200);
  --color-neutral-300: var(--neutral-300);
  --color-neutral-400: var(--neutral-400);
  --color-neutral-500: var(--neutral-500);
  --color-neutral-600: var(--neutral-600);
  --color-neutral-700: var(--neutral-700);
  --color-neutral-800: var(--neutral-800);
  --color-neutral-900: var(--neutral-900);
  --color-neutral-950: var(--neutral-950);
  --color-success: var(--success);
  --color-warning: var(--warning);
  --color-error: var(--error);
  --color-info: var(--info);

  /* Fonts */
  --font-sans: var(--font-geist-sans);
  --font-mono: var(--font-geist-mono);

  /* Spacing — extend when Figma uses non-standard values */
  /* e.g. --spacing-18: 4.5rem; */

  /* Border Radius */
  --radius-sm: var(--radius-sm);
  --radius-md: var(--radius-md);
  --radius-lg: var(--radius-lg);
  --radius-xl: var(--radius-xl);
  --radius-2xl: var(--radius-2xl);
  --radius-full: var(--radius-full);

  /* Shadows */
  --shadow-sm: var(--shadow-sm);
  --shadow-md: var(--shadow-md);
  --shadow-lg: var(--shadow-lg);
  --shadow-xl: var(--shadow-xl);
}

/* ── Base Resets ───────────────────────────────────────────────── */
body {
  background: var(--background);
  color: var(--foreground);
  font-family: var(--font-sans), system-ui, sans-serif;
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
}

/* Smooth scroll for anchor links */
html {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
}

/* Focus visible ring for accessibility */
*:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--brand-primary);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

### Token rules
- **When Figma uses a value not in the token system:** add a new CSS variable in
  `:root` AND a corresponding `@theme inline` entry. Commit the token before
  using it in a component.
- **Naming convention:** `--color-{category}-{shade}`, `--spacing-{name}`,
  `--radius-{size}`, `--shadow-{size}`.
- **NEVER skip the token layer.** `bg-brand-primary` ✅ · `bg-[#3a86ff]` ❌


## 4 · COMPONENT PATTERNS

### 4.1 Section Component Template

Every Figma section/frame follows this exact template:

```tsx
// components/sections/home/SectionName.tsx
import { SectionWrapper } from "@/components/ui/SectionWrapper";

export default function SectionName() {
  return (
    <SectionWrapper id="section-name" className="py-16 md:py-24 lg:py-32">
      {/* Section content */}
    </SectionWrapper>
  );
}
```

### 4.2 SectionWrapper (reusable)

```tsx
// components/ui/SectionWrapper.tsx
interface SectionWrapperProps {
  children: React.ReactNode;
  id?: string;
  className?: string;
  as?: React.ElementType;
}

export function SectionWrapper({
  children,
  id,
  className = "",
  as: Component = "section",
}: SectionWrapperProps) {
  return (
    <Component id={id} className={`w-full ${className}`}>
      <div className="mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        {children}
      </div>
    </Component>
  );
}
```

### 4.3 Page Assembly

```tsx
// app/page.tsx
import Hero from "@/components/sections/home/Hero";
import Features from "@/components/sections/home/Features";
import Pricing from "@/components/sections/home/Pricing";
import Testimonials from "@/components/sections/home/Testimonials";
import CTA from "@/components/sections/shared/CTA";

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <main>
      <Hero />
      <Features />
      <Pricing />
      <Testimonials />
      <CTA />
    </main>
  );
}
```

### 4.4 Server vs Client Components

| Default                      | Use `"use client"` when…                   |
|------------------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| All components are **Server** | useState, useEffect, useRef                |
| by default in App Router     | Event handlers (onClick, onChange, etc.)    |
|                              | Browser APIs (window, localStorage, etc.)  |
|                              | Intersection Observer, animations          |
|                              | Third-party client-only libraries          |

**Rule:** Keep the `"use client"` boundary as low in the tree as possible.
Extract only the interactive part into a small client component and keep the
parent as a server component.


## 5 · TAILWIND CSS USAGE RULES

### 5.1 Strict class ordering (Logical groups)

Follow this ordering in every `className`:
1. **Layout** → `flex`, `grid`, `block`, `inline-flex`
2. **Position** → `relative`, `absolute`, `sticky`, `fixed`
3. **Box model** → `w-`, `h-`, `min-w-`, `max-w-`, `p-`, `m-`
4. **Typography** → `text-`, `font-`, `leading-`, `tracking-`
5. **Background / Border** → `bg-`, `border-`, `rounded-`
6. **Effects** → `shadow-`, `opacity-`, `blur-`
7. **Transitions** → `transition-`, `duration-`, `ease-`
8. **State variants** → `hover:`, `focus:`, `active:`, `group-hover:`
9. **Responsive** → `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`

### 5.2 Banned patterns

```
❌ NEVER DO THIS:
- text-[14px]          → use text-sm or a custom token
- bg-[#ff5733]         → define a token, then use bg-{token-name}
- w-[345px]            → use w-full, max-w-sm, or a token
- mt-[22px]            → use mt-5 or mt-6 (closest standard value)
- p-[30px]             → use p-7 or p-8 and adjust the token
- leading-[1.4]        → use leading-snug, leading-normal, or define a token
- tracking-[0.02em]    → use tracking-tight, tracking-wide, or define a token
- gap-[18px]           → use gap-4 or gap-5 or define a token
- rounded-[12px]       → use rounded-xl or define --radius-custom
- shadow-[...]         → define a --shadow-custom token
- h-[100vh]            → use h-screen or h-dvh
- from-[#...] to-[#...] → define gradient color tokens

✅ ALWAYS DO THIS:
- Use Tailwind's built-in scale values
- Add custom tokens to @theme inline {} when no suitable value exists
- Reference tokens via their Tailwind utility name
```

### 5.3 Responsive breakpoints

| Prefix | Width    | Target               |
|--------|----------|----------------------|
| (none) | 0px+     | Mobile (default)     |
| `sm:`  | 640px+   | Large phones         |
| `md:`  | 768px+   | Tablets              |
| `lg:`  | 1024px+  | Small laptops        |
| `xl:`  | 1280px+  | Desktops             |
| `2xl:` | 1536px+  | Large desktops       |

**Mobile-first rule:** Write the mobile layout first with no prefix, then add
larger breakpoint overrides.

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — mobile-first
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4">

// ❌ Wrong — desktop-first
<div className="grid grid-cols-4 md:grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-1">
```

### 5.4 Container strategy

Never use `container` utility. Instead always use the `SectionWrapper` with
`max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8` for consistent page gutters.


## 6 · TYPOGRAPHY RULES

### 6.1 Font setup (already in layout.tsx)

```tsx
import { Geist, Geist_Mono } from "next/font/google";

const geistSans = Geist({ variable: "--font-geist-sans", subsets: ["latin"] });
const geistMono = Geist_Mono({ variable: "--font-geist-mono", subsets: ["latin"] });
```

If the Figma design uses a **different** font:
1. Import it via `next/font/google` or `next/font/local`.
2. Add the CSS variable to `<body>`.
3. Register it in `@theme inline { --font-{name}: var(--font-{name}-var); }`.
4. Use it with `font-{name}`.

### 6.2 Type scale mapping

Map Figma text styles to Tailwind utilities:

| Figma Style     | Tailwind Class                                    |
|-----------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| H1 / Hero       | `text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold`      |
| H2 / Section    | `text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold`      |
| H3 / Subsection | `text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold`               |
| H4              | `text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold`                |
| H5              | `text-lg sm:text-xl font-medium`                   |
| H6              | `text-base sm:text-lg font-medium`                 |
| Body Large      | `text-lg leading-relaxed`                          |
| Body            | `text-base leading-relaxed`                        |
| Body Small      | `text-sm leading-relaxed`                          |
| Caption         | `text-xs leading-normal`                           |
| Overline        | `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest`  |

### 6.3 Semantic headings

Always use the correct HTML heading element (`h1`–`h6`) matching the visual
hierarchy. One `<h1>` per page. Style with Tailwind classes, not the element tag.

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<h2 className="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-foreground">

// ❌ Wrong — div masquerading as heading
<div className="text-3xl font-bold">
```


## 7 · IMAGE & MEDIA RULES

### 7.1 Always use next/image

```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

<Image
  src="/images/hero-illustration.webp"
  alt="Descriptive alt text for accessibility"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  className="w-full h-auto rounded-xl object-cover"
  priority  // for above-the-fold images
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 50vw, 33vw"
/>
```

### 7.2 Image rules
- **Always** set explicit `width` and `height` from the Figma frame.
- **Always** provide meaningful `alt` text.
- **Always** add `priority` to hero/LCP images.
- **Always** add `sizes` prop for responsive images.
- **Always** use `object-cover` or `object-contain` as appropriate.
- **Prefer** WebP format. Export from Figma as WebP.
- **Store** images in `public/images/` with descriptive kebab-case names.


## 8 · ICONS (react-icons)

### 8.1 Usage

```tsx
import { HiArrowRight } from "react-icons/hi2";      // Heroicons v2
import { FiCheck } from "react-icons/fi";              // Feather Icons
import { RiStarFill } from "react-icons/ri";            // Remix Icons

<HiArrowRight className="size-5 text-brand-primary" aria-hidden="true" />
```

### 8.2 Icon rules
- Use `size-{n}` (Tailwind's `width` + `height` shorthand) for sizing.
- Always add `aria-hidden="true"` for decorative icons.
- For actionable icons (buttons), wrap in `<button>` with `aria-label`.
- Color icons with `text-{token}` classes.
- Prefer these icon sets (in order): **Heroicons v2** (`hi2`), **Lucide** (`lu`),
  **Feather** (`fi`), **Remix** (`ri`). Match the icon set used in Figma.
- **Never** use inline SVG when the icon exists in react-icons.


## 9 · ACCESSIBILITY (a11y)

### 9.1 Mandatory practices

| Rule                           | Implementation                                   |
|--------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Semantic HTML                  | Use `<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`, `<article>` |
| Heading hierarchy              | One `<h1>` per page; sequential `<h2>`→`<h6>`   |
| Alt text                       | Every `<Image>` must have descriptive `alt`      |
| Keyboard navigation            | All interactive elements focusable & operable    |
| Focus indicators               | Never remove `outline`; use `focus-visible:`     |
| Color contrast                 | WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1 normal, 3:1 large text)  |
| ARIA labels                    | Buttons/links with icon-only content → `aria-label` |
| Reduced motion                 | `motion-reduce:` variant for all animations      |
| Form labels                    | Every `<input>` has a visible `<label>`          |
| Link text                      | No "click here" — use descriptive text           |


## 10 · ANIMATIONS & TRANSITIONS

### 10.1 Rules
- **Default transition:** `transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out`
- **Hover states:** Subtle scale, color shift, or shadow changes.
- **Scroll animations:** Use Intersection Observer via a custom hook.
- **ALWAYS** add `motion-reduce:transition-none` or `motion-reduce:animate-none`
  alongside any animation for accessibility.
- **Never** use CSS `@keyframes` in components. Define them in `globals.css`
  and register them in `@theme inline`.
- **Performance:** Only animate `transform` and `opacity`. Never animate
  `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin`, or `padding`.

### 10.2 Scroll-reveal hook

```tsx
// hooks/useIntersectionObserver.ts
"use client";
import { useEffect, useRef, useState } from "react";

interface UseIntersectionObserverOptions {
  threshold?: number;
  rootMargin?: string;
  triggerOnce?: boolean;
}

export function useIntersectionObserver({
  threshold = 0.1,
  rootMargin = "0px",
  triggerOnce = true,
}: UseIntersectionObserverOptions = {}) {
  const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
  const [isIntersecting, setIsIntersecting] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    const element = ref.current;
    if (!element) return;

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      ([entry]) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          setIsIntersecting(true);
          if (triggerOnce) observer.unobserve(element);
        }
      },
      { threshold, rootMargin }
    );

    observer.observe(element);
    return () => observer.disconnect();
  }, [threshold, rootMargin, triggerOnce]);

  return { ref, isIntersecting };
}
```

### 10.3 Fade-up pattern

```tsx
"use client";
import { useIntersectionObserver } from "@/hooks/useIntersectionObserver";

export default function AnimatedSection() {
  const { ref, isIntersecting } = useIntersectionObserver();

  return (
    <div
      ref={ref}
      className={`
        transition-all duration-700 ease-out
        motion-reduce:transition-none
        ${isIntersecting
          ? "translate-y-0 opacity-100"
          : "translate-y-8 opacity-0"
        }
      `}
    >
      {/* Content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```


## 11 · PERFORMANCE RULES

### 11.1 Core Web Vitals targets

| Metric | Target   |
|--------|----------|
| LCP    | < 2.5s   |
| INP    | < 200ms  |
| CLS    | < 0.1    |

### 11.2 Mandatory optimisations

1. **Server Components by default.** Only add `"use client"` when necessary.
2. **next/image** for all images — never use raw `<img>`.
3. **next/font** for fonts — never use `<link>` to Google Fonts.
4. **Dynamic imports** for heavy client components:
   ```tsx
   import dynamic from "next/dynamic";
   const HeavyChart = dynamic(() => import("@/components/shared/Chart"), {
     ssr: false,
     loading: () => <div className="h-64 animate-pulse rounded-xl bg-neutral-200" />,
   });
   ```
5. **Preload critical assets** — use `priority` on hero images.
6. **Avoid layout shift** — always set dimensions on images and embeds.
7. **Lazy load below-the-fold sections** when they include heavy components.
8. **Minimize client-side JavaScript** — avoid pulling large libraries into
   client bundles.


## 12 · SEO RULES

### 12.1 Metadata (per page)

```tsx
// app/page.tsx (or any route page.tsx)
import type { Metadata } from "next";

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Page Title — Axiler",
  description: "Compelling meta description under 160 characters.",
  openGraph: {
    title: "Page Title — Axiler",
    description: "Compelling meta description.",
    url: "https://axiler.com",
    siteName: "Axiler",
    images: [
      {
        url: "/images/og-image.jpg",
        width: 1200,
        height: 630,
        alt: "Axiler Open Graph Image",
      },
    ],
    locale: "en_US",
    type: "website",
  },
  twitter: {
    card: "summary_large_image",
    title: "Page Title — Axiler",
    description: "Compelling meta description.",
    images: ["/images/og-image.jpg"],
  },
};
```

### 12.2 Semantic structure

- One `<h1>` per page.
- Sequential heading hierarchy: `<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>`.
- Use `<main id="main-content">` for skip-link target.
- Use `<nav aria-label="Main navigation">` for navbars.
- Use `<section aria-labelledby="section-heading-id">` with matching heading id.


## 13 · COMPONENT CODING STANDARDS

### 13.1 Props interface

Always define a TypeScript interface for component props:

```tsx
interface FeatureCardProps {
  icon: React.ReactNode;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  className?: string;
}

export function FeatureCard({ icon, title, description, className = "" }: FeatureCardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={`flex flex-col items-start gap-4 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-shadow duration-300 hover:shadow-md ${className}`}>
      <div className="flex size-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-brand-primary/10 text-brand-primary">
        {icon}
      </div>
      <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">{title}</h3>
      <p className="text-sm leading-relaxed text-neutral-600">{description}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 13.2 cn() utility for conditional classes

```tsx
// lib/utils.ts
export function cn(...classes: (string | boolean | undefined | null)[]) {
  return classes.filter(Boolean).join(" ");
}

// Usage
<div className={cn(
  "flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg px-4 py-2",
  variant === "primary" && "bg-brand-primary text-white",
  variant === "outline" && "border border-neutral-300 text-foreground",
  className
)} />
```

### 13.3 Button component template

```tsx
// components/ui/Button.tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";

interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "outline" | "ghost";
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Button({
  variant = "primary",
  size = "md",
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        "inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-all duration-300 focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-brand-primary disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
        // Variants
        variant === "primary" && "bg-brand-primary text-white hover:bg-brand-primary-dark active:scale-[0.98]",
        variant === "secondary" && "bg-brand-secondary text-white hover:opacity-90",
        variant === "outline" && "border border-neutral-300 bg-transparent text-foreground hover:bg-neutral-100",
        variant === "ghost" && "bg-transparent text-foreground hover:bg-neutral-100",
        // Sizes
        size === "sm" && "h-9 px-3 text-sm",
        size === "md" && "h-11 px-5 text-base",
        size === "lg" && "h-13 px-7 text-lg",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```


## 14 · FIGMA-TO-CODE WORKFLOW (Section by Section)

### Step 1: Inspect the Figma Section
- Note the **frame width** (desktop reference) and content layout.
- Extract all **colors** → map to tokens or create new ones.
- Extract all **font sizes, weights, line heights** → map to Tailwind scale.
- Extract all **spacing** (padding, gap, margin) → map to Tailwind spacing scale.
- Extract all **border radii, shadows** → map to tokens.
- Note **responsive** behaviour (auto-layout, constraints, min/max).

### Step 2: Create the Token (if needed)
- Add any new CSS variable to `:root` in `globals.css`.
- Add corresponding entry in `@theme inline { }`.

### Step 3: Build Atomic Components
- If the section needs a reusable element (card, button, badge), build it in
  `components/ui/` first.

### Step 4: Build the Section Component
- Create the file in `components/sections/{page-or-shared}/SectionName.tsx`.
- Use `SectionWrapper` for consistent padding/max-width.
- Build mobile-first, then add breakpoint variants.
- Verify at all 6 breakpoints (0, 640, 768, 1024, 1280, 1536px).

### Step 5: Assemble into Page
- Import the section in `app/page.tsx` (or the relevant route).
- Ensure section ordering matches Figma.

### Step 6: Test & Validate
- **Visual diff** against Figma at mobile, tablet, and desktop.
- Run Lighthouse audit → score 90+ on all categories.
- Check keyboard navigation and screen reader flow.
- Validate no arbitrary Tailwind values remain.


## 15 · NAMING CONVENTIONS

| Item                | Convention          | Example                      |
|---------------------|---------------------|------------------------------|
| Component files     | PascalCase.tsx      | `FeatureCard.tsx`            |
| Section files       | PascalCase.tsx      | `Hero.tsx`                   |
| Utility files       | camelCase.ts        | `formatDate.ts`              |
| Hook files          | camelCase.ts        | `useMediaQuery.ts`           |
| CSS variables       | kebab-case          | `--brand-primary`            |
| Tailwind tokens     | kebab-case          | `bg-brand-primary`           |
| Image files         | kebab-case          | `hero-illustration.webp`     |
| Route directories   | kebab-case          | `about-us/`                  |
| Constants           | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE    | `MAX_ITEMS_PER_PAGE`         |
| TypeScript types    | PascalCase          | `FeatureCardProps`           |
| ID attributes       | kebab-case          | `id="hero-section"`          |


## 16 · CODE QUALITY CHECKLIST (Before Every PR)

- [ ] Zero arbitrary/raw Tailwind values
- [ ] All colors reference design tokens
- [ ] Mobile-first responsive: works at 320px → 1536px+
- [ ] All images use `next/image` with width, height, alt, sizes
- [ ] Icons use `react-icons` with `aria-hidden` or `aria-label`
- [ ] Semantic HTML (`<section>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<main>`)
- [ ] One `<h1>` per page, correct heading order
- [ ] Focus-visible styles on all interactive elements
- [ ] `motion-reduce:` variants on all animations
- [ ] No `"use client"` unless strictly necessary
- [ ] TypeScript — no `any` types, all props typed
- [ ] Console.log statements removed
- [ ] Metadata (title, description, OG) set per page
- [ ] Lighthouse: Performance ≥ 90, Accessibility ≥ 95, SEO ≥ 95
- [ ] No layout shift (CLS < 0.1)
- [ ] Tested on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- [ ] All section components wrapped in `SectionWrapper`


## 17 · FORBIDDEN PATTERNS

```
❌ Inline styles              → style={{ color: "red" }}
❌ Raw <img> tags              → Use next/image Image component
❌ Raw <a> tags for internal   → Use next/link Link component
❌ Arbitrary Tailwind values   → text-[14px], bg-[#fff], w-[350px]
❌ !important in Tailwind      → !text-red-500
❌ CSS Modules for layout      → Use Tailwind utilities exclusively
❌ External CSS libraries      → No Bootstrap, Material UI, etc.
❌ Untyped props               → Always define TypeScript interfaces
❌ console.log in production   → Remove or use debug utility
❌ Div soup                    → Use semantic HTML elements
❌ Desktop-first responsive    → Always write mobile-first
❌ Hardcoded strings           → Extract to constants or CMS
❌ Unused imports              → Clean up every file
❌ Default exports for components → Use named exports (exception: page/layout)
❌ Giant monolithic components → Break into sub-components (< 150 lines)
❌ Nested ternaries            → Extract to variables or functions
```


## 18 · DARK MODE SUPPORT

If the Figma design includes a dark mode:

1. Define dark tokens in `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` block in `:root`.
2. Use `dark:` variant prefix for dark-specific overrides:
   ```tsx
   <div className="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 text-foreground">
   ```
3. Ensure all color tokens have dark variants.
4. Test both modes at every breakpoint.

If dark mode is NOT in the Figma design, only implement the light theme but
**still define** the dark CSS custom properties for future use.


## 19 · DEPLOYMENT & BUILD CHECKS

Before shipping:
```bash
# Type checking
npx tsc --noEmit

# Lint
npm run lint

# Production build (catches build-time errors)
npm run build

# Lighthouse CI (via Chrome DevTools or npx unlighthouse)
# Target: Perf ≥ 90, A11y ≥ 95, SEO ≥ 95, Best Practices ≥ 95
```


## 20 · SUMMARY — THE 10 COMMANDMENTS

1. **Thou shalt not use arbitrary Tailwind values.**
2. **Thou shalt define all design values as tokens.**
3. **Thou shalt build mobile-first, always.**
4. **Thou shalt use semantic HTML elements.**
5. **Thou shalt use `next/image` and `next/font`.**
6. **Thou shalt use `react-icons` for all icons.**
7. **Thou shalt type all props with TypeScript interfaces.**
8. **Thou shalt keep components under 150 lines.**
9. **Thou shalt respect accessibility (WCAG AA).**
10. **Thou shalt test at every breakpoint before shipping.**
